<b>Style Notes for Sort Names</b>

<p>

Sort name is the name that will be used when the artist is listed in a 
list with other artists, so that all the artists that start with <i>The</i>
will not end up under T. This also applies to artists who have a regular
names like <i>Eric Clapton</i> but not bands that have
ficticious names like <i>Cypress Hill</i>. Sort names should contain all 
the accented characters that are present in the name of the artist.

<p>
Non-english articles like <i>La</i>, <i>El</i>, <i>Los</i>, <i>Le</i>
should be treated like the english aritcle <i>The</i>. Artists with
the letters <i>DJ</i> (for Disc Jockey) should not include any
periods for the <i>DJ</i> portion in the name or sort name. Prefix titles like
<i>Dr.</i> should be treated as if they were first names. 

<p>
<b>Sort Name Examples:</b><br>
<blockquote>
<table width="100%">
      <tr>
         <td width=50%>
         <b>Name</b>
         </td>
         <td width=50%>
         <b>Sort Name</b>
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         The Beatles
         </td>
         <td valign=top>
         Beatles, The
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         Eric Clapton 
         </td>
         <td valign=top>
         Clapton, Eric
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         Cypress Hill 
         </td>
         <td valign=top>
         Cypress Hill
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         Bob Marley and the Wailers
         </td>
         <td valign=top>
         Marley, Bob and the Wailers
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         DJ Tiesto
         </td>
         <td  valign=top>
         Tiesto, DJ
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         Los Lobos
         </td>
         <td valign=top>
         Lobos, Los
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
         Dr. Demento
         </td>
         <td valign=top>
         Demento, Dr.
         </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
         <td valign=top>
